## Why This Is Asked

This question tests the ability to design a compliant, end-to-end Azure Fundamentals stack with a focus on PII privacy in telemetry—a common requirement in real-world enterprise roles.

## Key Concepts

- **TelemetryProcessors and TelemetryInitializers** in Application Insights
- **Frontend vs. backend** data masking strategies
- **PII redaction** in logs and events
- **Governance**: lightweight policy checks and CI gates to enforce compliance

## Code Example

```javascript
// Frontend: Application Insights TelemetryInitializer
import { TelemetryInitializer } from '@microsoft/applicationinsights-web';

const piiRedactionInitializer = (envelope) => {
  const maskEmail = (value) => value?.replace(/[\w.-]+@[\w.-]+\.\w+/g, '[EMAIL_REDACTED]');
  const maskPhone = (value) => value?.replace(/\b\d{3}[-.]?\d{3}[-.]?\d{4}\b/g, '[PHONE_REDACTED]');

  if (envelope.data?.properties) {
    const props = envelope.data.properties;
    for (const key in props) {
      if (props[key]) {
        props[key] = maskPhone(maskEmail(props[key]));
      }
    }
  }
  return true;
};

appInsights.addTelemetryInitializer(piiRedactionInitializer);
```

```csharp
// Backend: Azure Functions TelemetryProcessor
using Microsoft.ApplicationInsights.Channel;
using Microsoft.ApplicationInsights.Extensibility;

public class PiiScrubbingProcessor : ITelemetryProcessor
{
    private readonly ITelemetryProcessor _next;
    private static readonly Regex EmailRegex = new(@"[\w.-]+@[\w.-]+\.\w+", RegexOptions.Compiled);
    private static readonly Regex PhoneRegex = new(@"\b\d{3}[-.]?\d{3}[-.]?\d{4}\b", RegexOptions.Compiled);

    public PiiScrubbingProcessor(ITelemetryProcessor next) => _next = next;

    public void Process(ITelemetry item)
    {
        if (item is RequestTelemetry request)
        {
            request.Name = Sanitize(request.Name);
        }
        if (item is TraceTelemetry trace)
        {
            trace.Message = Sanitize(trace.Message);
        }
        _next.Process(item);
    }

    private string Sanitize(string value) =>
        PhoneRegex.Replace(
            EmailRegex.Replace(value, "[EMAIL_REDACTED]"),
            "[PHONE_REDACTED]"
        );
}
```

## Governance & Enforcement

